      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(update): respect explicit beta channel without fallback to latest",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nFixed an issue where `openclaw update --channel beta` would not return the latest beta version when the stable version had a higher semantic version number.\r\n\r\nWhen a user explicitly specifies `--channel beta`, the code now returns the beta tag version directly instead of comparing it with the latest tag and potentially falling back to the stable version.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- Removed the special beta channel comparison logic from `resolveNpmChannelTag` function in `src/infra/update-check.ts`\r\n- Updated test cases in `src/infra/update-check.test.ts` to reflect the new behavior\r\n- Removed the `fallbackToLatest` variable and related logic from `src/cli/update-cli/update-command.ts`\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n**Before the fix:**\r\n```bash\r\nopenclaw update --channel beta --dry-run\r\n# If latest version is higher than beta (e.g., stable 2026.3.30 > beta 2026.3.30 beta 4)\r\n# Would return the latest version instead of beta\r\n```\r\n\r\n**After the fix:**\r\n```bash\r\nopenclaw update --channel beta --dry-run\r\n# Always returns the version from the beta tag\r\n<img width=\"1352\" height=\"381\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/56a0aafb-91c0-440f-b69f-11f7e32d2c4c\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- Updated test cases in `src/infra/update-check.test.ts` to verify beta channel returns beta tag version\r\n- Removed unnecessary fallback logic\r\n- Total changes: 3 files, 5 insertions(+), 26 deletions(-)\r\n\r\nFixes: #88954",
